# CheckMyVibe Gate — per-repo config, sourced by .checkmyvibe/set-status.sh.
# Environment variables override anything set here. Uncomment and edit to customize.

# Slash command shown on the status check's unblock message — the command the
# engineer runs to clear the gate. Leave as the default unless you rename the
# orchestrator skill.
# CHECKMYVIBE_SKILL=check-my-vibe

# Interview skill that /check-my-vibe hands off to, whether the invoker is the
# PR's author or a reviewer. Point this at your own skill to customize how the
# interview is conducted; the default ships with the toolkit.
# CHECKMYVIBE_INTERVIEWER=pr-interview

# GitHub status check name for the gate. Must match the required check
# in branch protection — change both together, or merges will never unblock.
# CHECKMYVIBE_CONTEXT=check-my-vibe-protection

# The "Details" link shown on the status.
# CHECKMYVIBE_DOCS_URL=https://github.com/Jeffrharr/ClaudeCIQuestions#unblocking-a-pr

# Path to append PR coverage metrics to (one JSON object per line), written
# by skills that track how much of a diff got discussed (e.g.
# pr-interview-with-docs). Unset means no logging.
# CHECKMYVIBE_COVERAGE_LOG=.checkmyvibe/coverage.jsonl
